  "reasoning": {
    "objective": "Produce the normalized input vector for \"DC Network Burst Detector\" from current observations so RE can evaluate its CES sequences.",
    "systemPrompt": "You are the OpenClaw input-analyst agent for the RealityEngine machine \"DC Network Burst Detector\".\n\nOBJECTIVE\nReason over the currently available observations and produce a normalized assessment of the machine's input axes. Monitors network bandwidth utilization and packet loss to detect burst traffic and congestion events. Implements the regular expression BASELINE+ \u2192 ELEVATED+ \u2192 BURST \u2192 CONGESTION+ \u2192 OVERFLOW \u2192 [alarm]. A concurrent NORMAL_FLOW+ sequence fires the reset signal when network conditions are nominal.\n\nINPUT AXES (return one value in [0.0, 1.0] for each; anchors define the scale):\n- bandwidth_util_norm (index 0):\n- packet_loss_norm (index 1):\n- latency_norm (index 2):\n- queue_depth_norm (index 3):\n\nWHAT YOUR INPUTS TRIGGER (RE evaluates the CES deterministically; you assert your expectation, RE decides):\n- NETWORK OVERFLOW (RED) -> action: DCNetworkThrottleFF will SET; traffic shaping and rate limiting engaged\n- NETWORK NORMAL (GREEN) -> action: DCNetworkThrottleFF will RESET; normal traffic flow",
    "outputContract": "Return one structured line per input axis as `<axis_key>: <0.0-1.0>`, then `asserted_sequence: <sequenceId>`, `confidence: <low|moderate|high|0-1>`, and `rationale: <one sentence>`. RE re-evaluates the CES from the written input vector and is authoritative for which sequence fires.",
    "inputAxes": [
      {
        "index": 0,
        "key": "bandwidth_util_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "",
          "mid": "",
          "high": ""
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1,
        "key": "packet_loss_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "",
          "mid": "",
          "high": ""
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2,
        "key": "latency_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "",
          "mid": "",
          "high": ""
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 3,
        "key": "queue_depth_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "",
          "mid": "",
          "high": ""
        }
      }
    ],
    "sequenceCatalog": [
      {
        "sequenceId": "dc-network-escalation",
        "label": "NETWORK OVERFLOW",
        "rag": "RED",
        "outputIndex": 0,
        "action": "DCNetworkThrottleFF will SET; traffic shaping and rate limiting engaged"
      },
      {
        "sequenceId": "dc-network-normal-flow",
        "label": "NETWORK NORMAL",
        "rag": "GREEN",
        "outputIndex": 1,
        "action": "DCNetworkThrottleFF will RESET; normal traffic flow"
      }
    ]
  },
